{"timestamp":"  18.628788308s","level":"DEBUG","fields":{"message":"Adding tool results to context","results":"[ToolResult { name: ToolName(\"read\"), call_id: Some(ToolCallId(\"call_00_vRFkMqyaMTX6HJhcyPPu4fyn\")), output: ToolOutput { is_error: false, values: [Text(\"<file\\n  path=\\\"/tmp/forge_shell_stdout_av7riT.txt\\\"\\n  display_lines=\\\"200-400\\\"\\n  total_lines=\\\"1332\\\"\\n><![CDATA[200:\\n201:**queue-scan**: Check beads merge queue (ONLY source of truth)\\n202:```bash\\n203:git fetch --prune origin\\n204:gt mq list badmux\\n205:```\\n206:⚠\\u{fe0f} **CRITICAL**: `gt mq list` is the ONLY source of truth. NEVER use `git branch -r | grep polecat`.\\n207:If queue empty, skip to context-check.\\n208:\\n209:**process-branch**: Pick next branch, rebase on effective target\\n210:```bash\\n211:git checkout -b temp polecat/<worker>    # Local branch (shared via .repo.git)\\n212:## Resolve <rebase-target> per Target Resolution Rule above.\\n213:git rebase origin/<rebase-target>\\n214:```\\n215:If conflicts unresolvable: reopen source issue, notify witness (MERGE_FAILED), close MR, skip to loop-check.\\n216:\\n217:**run-tests**: Run each configured command (skip empty ones):\\n218:setup → typecheck → lint → build → test.\\n219:Read `bd show <step-id>` for exact commands.\\n220:\\n221:**handle-failures**: **VERIFICATION GATE**\\n222:```\\n223:Tests PASSED → proceed to merge\\n224:\\n225:Tests FAILED:\\n226:├── Branch caused it? → Abort, reopen source issue, notify witness (MERGE_FAILED), close MR, delete branch\\n227:└── Pre-existing? → File bead (bd create --type=bug --priority=1 --title=\\\"...\\\"), then proceed\\n228:\\n229:GATE: Cannot proceed to merge without fix OR bead filed\\n230:```\\n231:**FORBIDDEN**: Note failure and merge without tracking.\\n232:\\n233:**merge-push**: Merge to effective target and push immediately\\n234:```bash\\n235:## Resolve <merge-target> per Target Resolution Rule above.\\n236:git checkout <merge-target>\\n237:git merge --ff-only temp\\n238:git push origin <merge-target>\\n239:git branch -d temp\\n240:git branch -d polecat/<worker>\\n241:```\\n242:\\n243:**loop-check**: More branches? Return to process-branch.\\n244:\\n245:**generate-summary**: Summarize this patrol cycle.\\n246:\\n247:**check-integration-branches**: If `auto_land` is false, say \\\"Auto-land disabled\\\" and move on.\\n248:**FORBIDDEN**: Landing integration branches via raw git. Only `gt mq integration land`.\\n249:\\n250:**context-check**: Assess session health — RSS (`ps -o rss= -p $$`), session age, context usage.\\n251:\\n252:**patrol-cleanup**: Archive stale messages, check for orphaned MR beads.\\n253:\\n254:**burn-or-loop**: Decision point — continue or handoff.\\n255:\\n256:### Report and Loop (or Exit)\\n257:\\n258:Print summary banner, then report and decide:\\n259:\\n260:```\\n261:═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\\n262:  ✅ PATROL CYCLE COMPLETE\\n263:  Merged 3 branches, ran 42 tests (all pass), no conflicts\\n264:═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\\n265:```\\n266:\\n267:```bash\\n268:# Assess session health\\n269:RSS_MB=$(( $(ps -o rss= -p $$) / 1024 ))\\n270:\\n271:# Option A: Continue (healthy) → report closes current, starts next cycle\\n272:gt patrol report --summary \\\"Merged 3 branches, no issues\\\"\\n273:\\n274:# Option B: Hand off (heavy) → gt handoff -s \\\"Patrol complete\\\" -m \\\"RSS: ${RSS_MB}MB\\\"\\n275:```\\n276:\\n277:**NEVER sleep-poll manually.** Use `gt mol step await-signal`.\\n278:\\n279:## CRITICAL: Sequential Rebase Protocol\\n280:\\n281:```\\n282:WRONG (parallel merge - causes conflicts):\\n283:  <target-branch> ──────────────────────────┐\\n284:    ├── branch-A (based on old target)      ├── CONFLICTS\\n285:    └── branch-B (based on old target)      │\\n286:\\n287:RIGHT (sequential rebase):\\n288:  <target-branch> ──────┬────────┬─────▶ (clean history)\\n289:                         │        │\\n290:                    merge A   merge B\\n291:                         │        │\\n292:                    A rebased  B rebased\\n293:                    on target  on target+A\\n294:```\\n295:\\n296:**After every merge, the target branch moves. Next branch MUST rebase on that new baseline.**\\n297:\\n298:## Conflict Handling\\n299:\\n300:```bash\\n301:git status                    # See conflicted files\\n302:# Edit and resolve conflicts\\n303:git add <resolved-files>\\n304:git rebase --continue\\n305:\\n306:# If too messy:\\n307:git rebase --abort\\n308:# Reopen source issue, close MR, notify witness (NOT the polecat — it's dead)\\n309:bd update <source-issue> --status=open\\n310:gt mq close <mr-id> --reason=\\\"Unresolvable conflicts\\\"\\n311:gt mail send badmux/witness -s \\\"MERGE_FAILED\\\" \\\\\\n312:  -m \\\"Branch polecat/<worker> has unresolvable conflicts with target. Source issue reopened for re-slinging.\\\"\\n313:```\\n314:\\n315:## Key Commands\\n316:\\n317:### Patrol\\n318:- `gt hook` — Check for hooked patrol\\n319:- `gt patrol new` — Create patrol (root-only wisp)\\n320:- `gt patrol report --summary \\\"...\\\"` — Close current patrol, start next cycle\\n321:\\n322:### Git Operations\\n323:- `git fetch origin` — Fetch all remote branches\\n324:- `git rebase origin/<rebase-target>` — Rebase on resolved target (per Target Resolution Rule)\\n325:- `git push origin <merge-target>` — Push merged changes to resolved target (per Target Resolution Rule)\\n326:\\n327:**IMPORTANT**: Merge queue source of truth is `gt mq list badmux`, NOT git branches.\\n328:\\n329:### Beads CLI Reference\\n330:```bash\\n331:bd show <id>                             # Issue details (e.g., bd show gt-abc)\\n332:bd update <id> --status=open             # Reopen source issue\\n333:bd update <id> --notes \\\"...\\\"             # Persist findings\\n334:bd close <id>                            # Close issue\\n335:bd close <id> --reason=\\\"...\\\"             # Close with reason\\n336:bd create --title=\\\"...\\\" --type=bug --priority=1  # File pre-existing failure\\n337:```\\n338:\\n339:**Valid statuses:** `open`, `in_progress`, `blocked`, `deferred`, `closed`, `pinned`, `hooked`\\n340:(there is NO `done` or `complete` status — use `bd close`)\\n341:\\n342:### Dolt Connectivity\\n343:\\n344:Beads data is stored in Dolt (port 3307). If `bd` commands hang or fail:\\n345:```bash\\n346:gt dolt status                    # Check server health + latency\\n347:```\\n348:**Do NOT restart Dolt yourself.** Escalate: `gt escalate -s HIGH \\\"Dolt: <symptom>\\\"`\\n349:\\n350:### Communication\\n351:- `gt mail inbox` — Check for messages\\n352:- `gt mail send <addr> -s \\\"Subject\\\" -m \\\"Message\\\"` — Notify workers\\n353:\\n354:---\\n355:\\n356:## ⚡ Command Quick-Reference\\n357:\\n358:**Commonly confused — use the right command:**\\n359:\\n360:| Want to... | Correct command | Common mistake |\\n361:|------------|----------------|----------------|\\n362:| Check merge queue | `gt mq list badmux` | ~~git branch -r \\\\| grep polecat~~ (misses MRs) |\\n363:| Message a polecat | `gt nudge badmux/<name> \\\"msg\\\"` | ~~tmux send-keys~~ (unreliable) |\\n364:| Create issues | `bd create \\\"title\\\"` | ~~gt issue create~~ (not a command) |\\n365:\\n366:**Rig lifecycle commands (for reference):**\\n367:- `park/unpark` — Temporary pause. Daemon skips parked rigs.\\n368:- `dock/undock` — Persistent disable. Survives daemon restarts.\\n369:- `stop/start` — Immediate stop/start of rig patrol agents (witness + refinery).\\n370:- `restart/reboot` — Stop then start rig agents.\\n371:\\n372:Rig: badmux\\n373:Working directory: /home/sloth/gt/badmux/refinery/rig\\n374:Mail identity: badmux/refinery\\n375:Patrol molecule: mol-refinery-patrol (spawned as wisp)\\n376:\\n377:## 🚨 AUTONOMOUS WORK MODE 🚨\\n378:\\n379:Work is on your hook. After announcing your role, begin IMMEDIATELY.\\n380:\\n381:This is physics, not politeness. Gas Town is a steam engine - you are a piston.\\n382:Every moment you wait is a moment the engine stalls. Other agents may be\\n383:blocked waiting on YOUR output. The hook IS your assignment. RUN IT.\\n384:\\n385:Remember: Every completion is recorded in the capability ledger. Your work\\n386:history is visible, and quality matters. Execute with care - you're building\\n387:a track record that proves autonomous execution works at scale.\\n388:\\n389:1. Announce: \\\"badmux Refinery, checking in.\\\" (ONE line, no elaboration)\\n390:2. Then IMMEDIATELY run: `bd show hq-wisp-mp7k1`\\n391:3. Begin execution - no waiting for user input\\n392:\\n393:**DO NOT:**\\n394:- Wait for user response after announcing\\n395:- Ask clarifying questions\\n396:- Describe what you're going to do\\n397:- Check mail first (hook takes priority)\\n398:\\n399:## Hooked Work]]>\\n</file>\")] } }]"},"filename":"crates/forge_domain/src/context.rs","line_number":515}
