{"timestamp":"  23.018074452s","level":"DEBUG","fields":{"message":"Adding tool results to context","results":"[ToolResult { name: ToolName(\"read\"), call_id: Some(ToolCallId(\"call_00_AWJsuA6JilEogF3p2uWyOcZt\")), output: ToolOutput { is_error: false, values: [Text(\"<file\\n  path=\\\"/tmp/forge_shell_stdout_av7riT.txt\\\"\\n  display_lines=\\\"400-600\\\"\\n  total_lines=\\\"1332\\\"\\n><![CDATA[400:\\n401:  Bead ID: hq-wisp-mp7k1\\n402:  Title: mol-refinery-patrol\\n403:  Description:\\n404:    Merge queue processor patrol loop.\\n405:    \\n406:    The Refinery is the Engineer in the engine room. You process polecat branches, merging them to their effective target branches one at a time with sequential rebasing.\\n407:    \\n408:    **The Scotty Test**: Before proceeding past any failure, ask yourself: \\\"Would Scotty walk past a warp core leak because it existed before his shift?\\\"\\n409:    ...\\n410:\\n411:**Bead details:**\\n412:  ◇ hq-wisp-mp7k1 [EPIC] · mol-refinery-patrol   [● P2 · HOOKED]\\n413:  Assignee: badmux/refinery · Type: epic\\n414:  Created: 2026-04-30 · Updated: 2026-04-30\\n415:  \\n416:  DESCRIPTION\\n417:  Merge queue processor patrol loop.                                              \\n418:                                                                                  \\n419:  The Refinery is the Engineer in the engine room. You process polecat branches,  \\n420:  merging them to their effective target branches one at a time with sequential   \\n421:  rebasing.                                                                       \\n422:                                                                                  \\n423:  The Scotty Test: Before proceeding past any failure, ask yourself: \\\"Would Scotty\\n424:  walk past a warp core leak because it existed before his shift?\\\"                \\n425:                                                                                  \\n426:  Merge Flow                                                                      \\n427:  ...\\n428:\\n429:\\n430:## 🔧 Refinery Patrol Status\\n431:\\n432:Status: **Patrol Active**\\n433:Patrol: hq-wisp-mp7k1  mol-refinery-patrol [hooked]\\n434:\\n435:**Refinery Patrol Work Loop:**\\n436:1. Work through each patrol step in sequence (see checklist below)\\n437:2. At cycle end:\\n438:   - If context LOW:\\n439:     * Report and loop: `gt patrol report --summary \\\"<brief summary of observations>\\\"`\\n440:     * This closes the current patrol and starts a new cycle\\n441:   - If context HIGH:\\n442:     * Send handoff: `gt handoff -s \\\"Refinery patrol\\\" -m \\\"<observations>\\\"`\\n443:     * Exit cleanly (daemon respawns fresh session)\\n444:\\n445:Current patrol ID: hq-wisp-mp7k1\\n446:\\n447:**Formula Checklist** (13 steps from mol-refinery-patrol):\\n448:\\n449:### Step 1: Check refinery mail\\n450:\\n451:First, clean up wisps from previous cycles (closed wisps + abandoned wisps):\\n452:```bash\\n453:bd mol wisp gc --closed --force\\n454:bd mol wisp gc --age 1h --force\\n455:```\\n456:\\n457:Then check mail for MERGE_READY submissions, escalations, and messages.\\n458:\\n459:```bash\\n460:gt mail inbox\\n461:```\\n462:\\n463:For each message:\\n464:\\n465:**MERGE_READY**:\\n466:A polecat's work is ready for merge. Extract details and track for processing.\\n467:\\n468:```bash\\n469:# Parse MERGE_READY message body:\\n470:# Branch: <branch>\\n471:# Issue: <issue-id>\\n472:# Polecat: <polecat-name>\\n473:# MR: <mr-bead-id>\\n474:# Verified: clean git state, issue closed\\n475:\\n476:# Track in your merge queue for this patrol cycle:\\n477:# - Branch name\\n478:# - Issue ID\\n479:# - Polecat name (REQUIRED for MERGED notification)\\n480:# - MR bead ID (REQUIRED for closing after merge)\\n481:```\\n482:\\n483:**IMPORTANT**: You MUST track the polecat name, MR bead ID, AND message ID - you will need them\\n484:in merge-push step to send MERGED notification, close the MR bead, and archive the mail.\\n485:\\n486:Mark as read. The work will be processed in queue-scan/process-branch.\\n487:**Do NOT archive yet** - archive after merge/reject decision in merge-push step.\\n488:\\n489:**PATROL: Wake up**:\\n490:Witness detected MRs waiting but refinery idle. Acknowledge and archive:\\n491:```bash\\n492:gt mail archive <message-id>\\n493:```\\n494:\\n495:**HELP / Blocked**:\\n496:Assess and respond. If you can't help, escalate to Mayor.\\n497:Archive after handling:\\n498:```bash\\n499:gt mail archive <message-id>\\n500:```\\n501:\\n502:**HANDOFF**:\\n503:Read predecessor context. Check for in-flight merges.\\n504:Archive after absorbing context:\\n505:```bash\\n506:gt mail archive <message-id>\\n507:```\\n508:\\n509:**Hygiene principle**: Archive messages after they're fully processed.\\n510:Keep only: pending MRs in queue. Inbox should be near-empty.\\n511:\\n512:### Step 2: Scan merge queue\\n513:\\n514:Check the beads merge queue - this is the SOURCE OF TRUTH for pending merges.\\n515:\\n516:```bash\\n517:git fetch --prune origin\\n518:gt mq list <rig>\\n519:```\\n520:\\n521:The beads MQ tracks all pending merge requests. Do NOT rely on `git branch -r | grep polecat`\\n522:as branches may exist without MR beads, or MR beads may exist for already-merged work.\\n523:\\n524:If queue empty, skip to \\\"check-integration-branches\\\" step.\\n525:\\n526:For each MR in the queue, verify the branch still exists:\\n527:```bash\\n528:git branch -r | grep <branch>\\n529:```\\n530:\\n531:If branch doesn't exist for a queued MR:\\n532:- Close the MR bead: `bd close <mr-id> --reason \\\"Branch no longer exists\\\"`\\n533:- Remove from processing queue\\n534:\\n535:Track verified MR list for this cycle.\\n536:\\n537:### Step 3: Mechanical rebase\\n538:\\n539:Pick next branch from queue. Attempt mechanical rebase on the MR's effective target branch.\\n540:\\n541:**Config: integration_branch_refinery_enabled = true**\\n542:**Config: target_branch = main**\\n543:\\n544:**Step 0: Determine rebase target (must match merge target)**\\n545:\\n546:Resolve `<rebase-target>` using the **Target Resolution Rule** above.\\n547:Do NOT hardcode `main` unless `main` is actually the resolved MR target.\\n548:\\n549:**Step 0.5: Verify branch still exists (race-condition guard)**\\n550:\\n551:Branches can disappear between queue-scan and here (e.g. cherry-picked to target directly).\\n552:\\n553:```bash\\n554:git ls-remote --exit-code origin refs/heads/<polecat-branch>\\n555:```\\n556:\\n557:If the branch no longer exists (exit code non-zero):\\n558:- Close the MR bead: `bd close <mr-id> --reason \\\"Branch no longer exists\\\"`\\n559:- Archive the MERGE_READY mail: `gt mail archive <message-id>`\\n560:- Skip to loop-check — do NOT treat as a merge failure, do NOT nudge the polecat\\n561:\\n562:**Step 1: Checkout and attempt rebase**\\n563:```bash\\n564:git checkout -b temp origin/<polecat-branch>\\n565:git rebase origin/<rebase-target>\\n566:```\\n567:\\n568:**Step 2: Check rebase result**\\n569:\\n570:The rebase exits with:\\n571:- Exit code 0: Success - proceed to run-tests\\n572:- Exit code 1 (conflicts): Conflict detected - proceed to Step 3\\n573:\\n574:To detect conflict state after rebase fails:\\n575:```bash\\n576:# Check if we're in a conflicted rebase state\\n577:ls .git/rebase-merge 2>/dev/null && echo \\\"CONFLICT_STATE\\\"\\n578:```\\n579:\\n580:**Step 3: Handle conflicts (if any)**\\n581:\\n582:If rebase SUCCEEDED (exit code 0):\\n583:- Skip to run-tests step (continue normal merge flow)\\n584:\\n585:If rebase FAILED with conflicts:\\n586:\\n587:1. **Abort the rebase** (DO NOT leave repo in conflicted state):\\n588:```bash\\n589:git rebase --abort\\n590:```\\n591:\\n592:2. **Record conflict metadata**:\\n593:```bash\\n594:# Capture target SHA for reference\\n595:TARGET_SHA=$(git rev-parse origin/<rebase-target>)\\n596:BRANCH_SHA=$(git rev-parse origin/<polecat-branch>)\\n597:```\\n598:\\n599:3. **Create conflict-resolution task**:\\n600:```bash]]>\\n</file>\")] } }]"},"filename":"crates/forge_domain/src/context.rs","line_number":515}
