{"timestamp":"  27.826894825s","level":"DEBUG","fields":{"message":"Adding tool results to context","results":"[ToolResult { name: ToolName(\"read\"), call_id: Some(ToolCallId(\"call_00_2kuH9cdkyAXo3jcmef4ZWafn\")), output: ToolOutput { is_error: false, values: [Text(\"<file\\n  path=\\\"/tmp/forge_shell_stdout_av7riT.txt\\\"\\n  display_lines=\\\"600-800\\\"\\n  total_lines=\\\"1332\\\"\\n><![CDATA[600:```bash\\n601:bd create --type=task --priority=1 --title=\\\"Resolve merge conflicts: <original-issue-title>\\\" --description=\\\"## Conflict Resolution Required\\n602:\\n603:Original MR: <mr-bead-id>\\n604:Branch: <polecat-branch>\\n605:Original Issue: <issue-id>\\n606:Conflict with target <rebase-target> at: ${TARGET_SHA}\\n607:Branch SHA: ${BRANCH_SHA}\\n608:\\n609:## Instructions\\n610:1. Clone/checkout the branch\\n611:2. Rebase on target: git rebase origin/<rebase-target>\\n612:3. Resolve conflicts\\n613:4. Force push: git push -f origin <branch>\\n614:5. Close this task when done\\n615:\\n616:The MR will be re-queued for processing after conflicts are resolved.\\\"\\n617:```\\n618:\\n619:4. **Skip this MR** (do NOT delete branch or close MR bead):\\n620:- Leave branch intact for conflict resolution\\n621:- Leave MR bead open (will be re-processed after resolution)\\n622:- Continue to loop-check for next branch\\n623:\\n624:**CRITICAL**: Never delete a branch that has conflicts. The branch contains\\n625:the original work and must be preserved for conflict resolution.\\n626:\\n627:Track: rebase result (success/conflict), conflict task ID if created.\\n628:\\n629:### Step 4: Run quality checks and tests\\n630:\\n631:**⚠ FIRST CHECK: If run_tests = \\\"false\\\", skip this ENTIRE step. Proceed directly to the next step. Do not run any quality checks or tests.**\\n632:\\n633:**Config: run_tests = true**\\n634:**Config: test_command = {{test_command}}**\\n635:**Config: setup_command = {{setup_command}}**\\n636:**Config: typecheck_command = {{typecheck_command}}**\\n637:**Config: lint_command = {{lint_command}}**\\n638:**Config: build_command = {{build_command}}**\\n639:\\n640:If run_tests is \\\"false\\\": STOP HERE. Skip everything below and proceed to the next step.\\n641:\\n642:**1. Run quality checks (skip any that are not configured):**\\n643:\\n644:If setup_command is set: `{{setup_command}}`\\n645:If typecheck_command is set: `{{typecheck_command}}`\\n646:If lint_command is set: `{{lint_command}}`\\n647:If build_command is set: `{{build_command}}`\\n648:\\n649:```bash\\n650:{{setup_command}}           # Make sure all newly added dependencies are installed (if command set)\\n651:{{typecheck_command}}       # Check for type errors (if command set)\\n652:{{lint_command}}            # Check for lint errors (if command set)\\n653:{{build_command}}           # Make sure it builds (if command set)\\n654:```\\n655:\\n656:Empty commands mean \\\"not configured for this project\\\" — skip silently.\\n657:\\n658:**2. If quality checks fail:**\\n659:\\n660:Proceed to handle-failures step. Track which specific check failed\\n661:(setup/typecheck/lint/build) for the failure diagnosis.\\n662:\\n663:**3. Run the test suite:**\\n664:\\n665:```bash\\n666:{{test_command}}            # Run tests (configured per-rig)\\n667:```\\n668:\\n669:Track results: pass count, fail count, specific failures.\\n670:\\n671:### Step 5: Quality review merge diff\\n672:\\n673:**Config: judgment_enabled = false**\\n674:**Config: review_depth = standard**\\n675:\\n676:Review the merge diff for quality issues. This step is measurement-only (Phase 1):\\n677:reviews are recorded but do NOT gate merges.\\n678:\\n679:**Step 1: Check if quality review is enabled**\\n680:\\n681:If judgment_enabled is not \\\"true\\\", skip this step entirely and proceed to\\n682:handle-failures. Log: \\\"Quality review skipped (judgment_enabled=false)\\\"\\n683:\\n684:**Step 2: Get the merge diff**\\n685:\\n686:```bash\\n687:git diff origin/main...temp\\n688:```\\n689:\\n690:If the diff is empty, skip with: \\\"No diff to review\\\"\\n691:\\n692:**Step 3: Review the diff**\\n693:\\n694:Review the diff yourself using your judgment. Assess:\\n695:\\n696:1. **Correctness**: Logic errors, off-by-one, nil/null handling, race conditions\\n697:2. **Security**: Injection, auth bypass, secrets in code, unsafe deserialization\\n698:3. **Clarity**: Naming, structure, comments where non-obvious\\n699:4. **Style**: Consistency with surrounding code, idiomatic patterns\\n700:\\n701:Depth is controlled by review_depth:\\n702:- `quick`: Focus on correctness and security only. Skim for obvious issues.\\n703:- `standard`: All four categories. Moderate detail.\\n704:- `deep`: Thorough line-by-line review. Flag even minor style issues.\\n705:\\n706:**Step 4: Score and recommend**\\n707:\\n708:Assign a score from 0.0 to 1.0:\\n709:- 0.9-1.0: Excellent — no issues or only trivial nits\\n710:- 0.7-0.89: Good — minor issues only\\n711:- 0.45-0.69: Needs work — significant issues found\\n712:- 0.0-0.44: Breach — critical issues (security, correctness)\\n713:\\n714:Recommendation:\\n715:- `approve`: Score >= 0.45\\n716:- `request_changes`: Score < 0.45\\n717:\\n718:**Step 5: Record the result as a wisp**\\n719:\\n720:Record the quality review result. This is fail-open: if the command fails,\\n721:log the error and continue — never block the merge.\\n722:\\n723:```bash\\n724:bd create \\\"quality-review: Score <score>, <recommendation>\\\" -t chore --ephemeral \\\\\\n725:  -l type:plugin-run,plugin:quality-review-result,worker:<polecat-name>,rig:<rig-name>,score:<score>,recommendation:<approve|request_changes>,result:success \\\\\\n726:  -d \\\"Score: <score>, <recommendation>. Issues: <count> (<summary>)\\\" \\\\\\n727:  --silent 2>/dev/null || true\\n728:```\\n729:\\n730:**Step 6: Handle breach scores (measurement-only)**\\n731:\\n732:If score < 0.45 (breach threshold):\\n733:- Add a note to your merge summary: \\\"Warning: Quality review breach (score: X.XX)\\\"\\n734:- List the critical/major issues found\\n735:- Do NOT block the merge — Phase 1 is measurement-only\\n736:- Proceed to handle-failures normally\\n737:\\n738:Track: review score, recommendation, issue count, duration.\\n739:\\n740:### Step 6: Handle quality check or test failures\\n741:\\n742:**VERIFICATION GATE**: This step enforces the Beads Promise.\\n743:\\n744:If all checks and tests PASSED: This step auto-completes. Proceed to merge.\\n745:\\n746:If any check or test FAILED:\\n747:1. Diagnose: Is this a branch regression or pre-existing on the target branch?\\n748:2. If branch caused it:\\n749:   - Abort merge (clean up temp branch)\\n750:   - **Send FIX_NEEDED directly to the polecat** (event-driven lifecycle):\\n751:     ```bash\\n752:     gt mail send <rig>/polecats/<polecat-name> -s \\\"FIX_NEEDED <polecat-name>\\\" --stdin <<'BODY'\\n753:     Branch: <branch>\\n754:     Issue: <issue-id>\\n755:     Polecat: <polecat-name>\\n756:     Rig: <rig>\\n757:     Target: <target-branch>\\n758:     Failed-At: $(date -u +%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ)\\n759:     Failure-Type: <tests|build|lint|typecheck>\\n760:     Error: <failure description/output>\\n761:     MR-Bead-ID: <mr-bead-id>\\n762:     Attempt-Number: <N>\\n763:     BODY\\n764:     ```\\n765:   - **Update the bead** with failure details so they survive session death:\\n766:     ```bash\\n767:     bd update <issue-id> --notes \\\"Merge failure (attempt <N>): <failure-type> - <error summary>\\\"\\n768:     ```\\n769:   - **Do NOT close the MR bead** — the polecat will resubmit\\n770:   - **Do NOT delete the branch** — the polecat needs it for the fix\\n771:   - **Do NOT reopen the source issue** — the polecat is still working on it\\n772:   - **Do NOT send MERGE_FAILED to witness** — FIX_NEEDED goes to polecat directly\\n773:   - Clean up temp branch and skip to loop-check:\\n774:     ```bash\\n775:     git checkout main\\n776:     git branch -D temp\\n777:     ```\\n778:   - Archive the MERGE_READY message\\n779:   - Skip to loop-check\\n780:3. If pre-existing on the target branch:\\n781:   - **DUPLICATE CHECK (MANDATORY)**: Before filing a new bug, search for existing open bugs:\\n782:     ```bash\\n783:     bd search \\\"<failure description>\\\" --status open --label gt:bug --limit 5\\n784:     ```\\n785:     If an existing open bug covers the same failure, do NOT create a duplicate.\\n786:     Instead, note the existing bead ID and proceed.\\n787:   - Only if NO existing bug matches: bd create --type=bug --priority=1 --title=\\\"Pre-existing failure: <description>\\\"\\n788:   - FORBIDDEN: Writing code to fix quality check or test failures. You merge branches, you do not develop.\\n789:   - Proceed with the merge if the failure is pre-existing (not caused by the branch).\\n790:\\n791:**FIX_NEEDED CHECKLIST** (all required before skipping to loop-check):\\n792:- [ ] FIX_NEEDED sent to polecat (with failure details)\\n793:- [ ] Bead updated with failure notes\\n794:- [ ] Temp branch cleaned up (NOT the polecat branch!)\\n795:- [ ] MERGE_READY message archived\\n796:\\n797:**GATE REQUIREMENT**: You CANNOT proceed to merge-push without:\\n798:- All quality checks and tests passing, OR\\n799:- Bead filed (or existing duplicate confirmed) for the pre-existing failure]]>\\n</file>\")] } }]"},"filename":"crates/forge_domain/src/context.rs","line_number":515}
