{"timestamp":"  35.167076300s","level":"DEBUG","fields":{"message":"Adding tool results to context","results":"[ToolResult { name: ToolName(\"read\"), call_id: Some(ToolCallId(\"call_00_9N08tRZuP7UoJC26lrMP6zVt\")), output: ToolOutput { is_error: false, values: [Text(\"<file\\n  path=\\\"/tmp/forge_shell_stdout_av7riT.txt\\\"\\n  display_lines=\\\"800-1100\\\"\\n  total_lines=\\\"1332\\\"\\n><![CDATA[ 800:\\n 801:FORBIDDEN: Writing application code, exploring polecat implementations, or\\n 802:re-implementing fixes. You are a mechanical merge processor.\\n 803:\\n 804:This is non-negotiable. Never disavow. Never \\\"note and proceed.\\\" \\n 805:\\n 806:### Step 7: Merge and push\\n 807:\\n 808:Merge and push. CRITICAL: Notifications come IMMEDIATELY after push.\\n 809:\\n 810:**Config: integration_branch_refinery_enabled = true**\\n 811:**Config: target_branch = main**\\n 812:**Config: delete_merged_branches = true**\\n 813:**Config: merge_strategy = direct**\\n 814:**Config: require_review = false**\\n 815:\\n 816:**Step 1: Merge (strategy-dependent)**\\n 817:\\n 818:Determine `<merge-target>` using the **Target Resolution Rule** above.\\n 819:\\n 820:**If merge_strategy = \\\"direct\\\" (default):**\\n 821:\\n 822:```bash\\n 823:git checkout <merge-target>\\n 824:git merge --ff-only temp\\n 825:git push origin <merge-target>\\n 826:```\\n 827:\\n 828:**Step 1.5 (direct only): VERIFY PUSH SUCCEEDED (CRITICAL - PATCH-003)**\\n 829:\\n 830:Push can fail silently (network, auth, hooks). IMMEDIATELY verify:\\n 831:```bash\\n 832:git fetch origin\\n 833:LOCAL_SHA=$(git rev-parse <merge-target>)\\n 834:REMOTE_SHA=$(git rev-parse origin/<merge-target>)\\n 835:echo \\\"Local:  $LOCAL_SHA\\\"\\n 836:echo \\\"Remote: $REMOTE_SHA\\\"\\n 837:```\\n 838:\\n 839:**If SHAs match**: Push succeeded.\\n 840:\\n 841:**Step 1.6 (direct only): CHECK FOR OPEN PR ON BRANCH (gas-fk4)**\\n 842:\\n 843:Before proceeding to post-merge cleanup (which deletes the remote branch),\\n 844:check if this branch has an open GitHub PR. Deleting the remote branch would\\n 845:cause GitHub to auto-close the PR as \\\"closed\\\" (not \\\"merged\\\"), destroying\\n 846:the PR audit trail and making it appear that work was rejected.\\n 847:\\n 848:```bash\\n 849:OPEN_PR=$(gh pr list --head <polecat-branch> --state open --json number --limit 1 2>/dev/null || echo \\\"[]\\\")\\n 850:if [ \\\"$OPEN_PR\\\" != \\\"[]\\\" ] && [ \\\"$OPEN_PR\\\" != \\\"\\\" ]; then\\n 851:  echo \\\"Open PR found on branch — will use --skip-branch-delete in post-merge\\\"\\n 852:  # Set flag for Step 3 (post-merge cleanup) to skip branch deletion\\n 853:  SKIP_BRANCH_DELETE=true\\n 854:fi\\n 855:```\\n 856:\\n 857:If an open PR exists, pass `--skip-branch-delete` to `gt mq post-merge` in Step 3.\\n 858:The PR should be merged or closed through the GitHub API, not by branch deletion.\\n 859:\\n 860:Continue to Step 2.\\n 861:\\n 862:**If SHAs differ**: STOP. Push failed silently.\\n 863:- DO NOT send MERGED notification\\n 864:- DO NOT close MR bead\\n 865:- DO NOT delete branch\\n 866:- Debug the push failure (check `git push` output, network, auth)\\n 867:- Retry push and verify again before proceeding\\n 868:\\n 869:**If merge_strategy = \\\"pr\\\":**\\n 870:\\n 871:Push the rebased branch and create a GitHub PR instead of direct merge.\\n 872:\\n 873:```bash\\n 874:# Push the rebased polecat branch (force-push since we rebased)\\n 875:git checkout temp\\n 876:git push origin temp:refs/heads/<polecat-branch> --force-with-lease\\n 877:\\n 878:# Create the PR using bead metadata for title/description\\n 879:PR_URL=$(gh pr create --base <merge-target> --head <polecat-branch> --title \\\"<issue-title> (<issue-id>)\\\" --body \\\"## Summary\\n 880:\\n 881:Automated merge from polecat branch.\\n 882:\\n 883:- **Issue**: <issue-id>\\n 884:- **Polecat**: <polecat-name>\\n 885:- **Branch**: <polecat-branch>\\n 886:- **Tests**: Passed (verified by refinery)\\n 887:\\n 888:---\\n 889:*Created by Gas Town Refinery*\\\")\\n 890:echo \\\"PR created: $PR_URL\\\"\\n 891:```\\n 892:\\n 893:If the PR already exists for this branch, `gh pr create` will fail. In that case,\\n 894:find the existing PR:\\n 895:```bash\\n 896:PR_URL=$(gh pr view <polecat-branch> --json url -q '.url')\\n 897:```\\n 898:\\n 899:**Step 1.5 (pr only): VERIFY PR CREATED**\\n 900:\\n 901:```bash\\n 902:gh pr view <polecat-branch> --json url,state -q '.url + \\\" \\\" + .state'\\n 903:```\\n 904:\\n 905:If the PR was not created or is in an unexpected state, debug and retry.\\n 906:\\n 907:**Step 1.6 (pr only): WAIT FOR CI CHECKS TO PASS**\\n 908:\\n 909:⚠\\u{fe0f} **DO NOT PROCEED until CI passes. DO NOT send MERGED until the PR is actually merged.**\\n 910:\\n 911:```bash\\n 912:# Get the repo URL for gh commands\\n 913:REPO_URL=$(git remote get-url origin | sed 's/.*github.com[:/]\\\\(.*\\\\)\\\\.git/\\\\1/')\\n 914:\\n 915:# Wait for CI checks (timeout 15 minutes)\\n 916:gh pr checks <polecat-branch> --repo \\\"$REPO_URL\\\" --watch --fail-fast\\n 917:```\\n 918:\\n 919:**If CI checks FAIL:**\\n 920:Do NOT merge. Send FIX_NEEDED back to the polecat:\\n 921:```bash\\n 922:FAILURE_OUTPUT=$(gh pr checks <polecat-branch> --repo \\\"$REPO_URL\\\" 2>&1)\\n 923:gt mail send <rig>/polecats/<polecat-name> -s \\\"FIX_NEEDED <polecat-name>\\\" --stdin <<'BODY'\\n 924:Branch: <branch>\\n 925:Issue: <issue-id>\\n 926:PR: ${PR_URL}\\n 927:Failure-Type: ci-checks\\n 928:Error: $FAILURE_OUTPUT\\n 929:Attempt-Number: 1\\n 930:BODY\\n 931:```\\n 932:Then skip to Step 4 (archive mail) and continue patrol.\\n 933:\\n 934:**If CI checks PASS:**\\n 935:\\n 936:**Step 1.7 (pr only): CHECK REVIEW APPROVAL STATUS (gas-fk4)**\\n 937:\\n 938:⚠\\u{fe0f} **DO NOT merge a PR that has not been explicitly approved.**\\n 939:Plain review comments (COMMENTED) are NOT approval. Only an explicit\\n 940:\\\"APPROVED\\\" reviewDecision allows the merge to proceed.\\n 941:\\n 942:```bash\\n 943:REVIEW_DECISION=$(gh pr view <polecat-branch> --repo \\\"$REPO_URL\\\" --json reviewDecision -q '.reviewDecision')\\n 944:echo \\\"Review decision: $REVIEW_DECISION\\\"\\n 945:```\\n 946:\\n 947:| reviewDecision | Action |\\n 948:|----------------|--------|\\n 949:| `APPROVED` | Proceed to merge |\\n 950:| `CHANGES_REQUESTED` | Send FIX_NEEDED to polecat (reviewer rejected), skip merge |\\n 951:| `REVIEW_REQUIRED` or empty | PR has not been reviewed yet — skip merge, leave PR open |\\n 952:\\n 953:**If CHANGES_REQUESTED:**\\n 954:```bash\\n 955:gt mail send <rig>/polecats/<polecat-name> -s \\\"FIX_NEEDED <polecat-name>\\\" --stdin <<'BODY'\\n 956:Branch: <branch>\\n 957:Issue: <issue-id>\\n 958:PR: ${PR_URL}\\n 959:Failure-Type: review-rejected\\n 960:Error: Reviewer requested changes on the PR. Address the review feedback and resubmit.\\n 961:Attempt-Number: 1\\n 962:BODY\\n 963:```\\n 964:Clean up temp branch, archive MERGE_READY, skip to loop-check.\\n 965:\\n 966:**If REVIEW_REQUIRED or empty (not yet reviewed):**\\n 967:Do NOT merge. Do NOT close. Do NOT send FIX_NEEDED. Leave the PR open\\n 968:for human review. Archive the MERGE_READY mail — the PR will be picked\\n 969:up on a future patrol cycle if/when it gets approved.\\n 970:Clean up temp branch and skip to loop-check.\\n 971:\\n 972:**If APPROVED:**\\n 973:Merge the PR:\\n 974:```bash\\n 975:gh pr merge <polecat-branch> --repo \\\"$REPO_URL\\\" --merge --delete-branch\\n 976:```\\n 977:\\n 978:If merge fails (conflict, branch protection), debug and retry.\\n 979:\\n 980:⚠\\u{fe0f} **STOP HERE - DO NOT PROCEED UNTIL THE PR IS ACTUALLY MERGED ON GITHUB**\\n 981:\\n 982:**Step 2: Send MERGED Notification (REQUIRED - DO THIS IMMEDIATELY)**\\n 983:\\n 984:RIGHT NOW, before any cleanup, send MERGED mail to Witness.\\n 985:\\n 986:**If merge_strategy = \\\"direct\\\":**\\n 987:```bash\\n 988:gt mail send <rig>/witness -s \\\"MERGED <polecat-name>\\\" -m \\\"Branch: <branch>\\n 989:Issue: <issue-id>\\n 990:Merged-At: $(date -u +%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ)\\\"\\n 991:```\\n 992:\\n 993:**If merge_strategy = \\\"pr\\\":**\\n 994:```bash\\n 995:gt mail send <rig>/witness -s \\\"MERGED <polecat-name>\\\" -m \\\"Branch: <branch>\\n 996:Issue: <issue-id>\\n 997:PR: ${PR_URL}\\n 998:Merged-At: $(date -u +%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ)\\\"\\n 999:```\\n1000:\\n1001:Note: In PR mode, MERGED is only sent AFTER `gh pr merge` succeeds — the PR\\n1002:is actually merged on GitHub before the witness is notified.\\n1003:\\n1004:This signals the Witness to nuke the polecat worktree. WITHOUT THIS NOTIFICATION,\\n1005:POLECAT WORKTREES ACCUMULATE INDEFINITELY AND THE LIFECYCLE BREAKS.\\n1006:\\n1007:**Step 3: Post-merge cleanup (REQUIRED — single command)**\\n1008:\\n1009:This single command handles closing the MR bead, closing the source issue, and\\n1010:deleting the remote polecat branch (respects delete_merged_branches config):\\n1011:\\n1012:```bash\\n1013:# If an open PR was detected in Step 1.6 (direct) or merge_strategy=pr,\\n1014:# pass --skip-branch-delete to avoid auto-closing the PR via head_ref_delete.\\n1015:# Otherwise, omit the flag.\\n1016:gt mq post-merge <rig> <mr-bead-id>            # normal (no open PR)\\n1017:gt mq post-merge <rig> <mr-bead-id> --skip-branch-delete  # open PR exists\\n1018:```\\n1019:\\n1020:The MR bead ID was in the MERGE_READY message or find via:\\n1021:```bash\\n1022:bd list --type=merge-request --status=open | grep <polecat-name>\\n1023:```\\n1024:\\n1025:Verify the command output shows all steps succeeded (✓ for each).\\n1026:\\n1027:**Note**: In PR mode, the source branch is NOT deleted (it's the PR head branch).\\n1028:`delete_merged_branches` is ignored when merge_strategy=pr — the branch is cleaned\\n1029:up when the PR is merged on GitHub. The `--skip-branch-delete` flag (gas-fk4) also\\n1030:prevents branch deletion when an open PR is detected in direct merge mode.\\n1031:\\n1032:**Step 4: Archive the MERGE_READY mail (REQUIRED)**\\n1033:```bash\\n1034:gt mail archive <merge-ready-message-id>\\n1035:```\\n1036:The message ID was tracked when you processed inbox-check.\\n1037:\\n1038:**Step 5: Cleanup temp branch**\\n1039:```bash\\n1040:git branch -d temp\\n1041:```\\n1042:\\n1043:**VERIFICATION GATE**: You CANNOT proceed to loop-check without:\\n1044:- [x] MERGED mail sent to witness (with PR URL if merge_strategy=pr)\\n1045:- [x] Post-merge cleanup completed (MR closed, source issue closed, branch deleted)\\n1046:- [x] MERGE_READY mail archived\\n1047:\\n1048:If you skipped notifications or archiving, GO BACK AND DO THEM NOW.\\n1049:\\n1050:Target branch has moved. Any remaining branches need rebasing on new baseline.\\n1051:\\n1052:### Step 8: Check for more work\\n1053:\\n1054:More branches to process?\\n1055:\\n1056:**Entry paths:**\\n1057:- Normal: After successful merge-push\\n1058:- Conflict-skip: After process-branch created conflict-resolution task\\n1059:\\n1060:If yes: Return to process-branch with next branch.\\n1061:If no: Continue to generate-summary.\\n1062:\\n1063:**Track for this cycle:**\\n1064:- branches_merged: count and names of successfully merged branches\\n1065:- branches_conflict: count and names of branches skipped due to conflicts\\n1066:- conflict_tasks: IDs of conflict-resolution tasks created\\n1067:\\n1068:This tracking feeds into generate-summary for the patrol digest.\\n1069:\\n1070:### Step 9: Generate handoff summary\\n1071:\\n1072:Summarize this patrol cycle.\\n1073:\\n1074:**VERIFICATION**: Before generating summary, confirm for each merged branch:\\n1075:- [ ] MERGED mail was sent to witness\\n1076:- [ ] MR bead was closed\\n1077:- [ ] Source issue was closed\\n1078:- [ ] MERGE_READY mail archived\\n1079:\\n1080:If any notifications, closures, or archiving were missed, do them now!\\n1081:\\n1082:Include in summary:\\n1083:- Branches merged (count, names)\\n1084:- MERGED mails sent (count - should match branches merged)\\n1085:- MR beads closed (count - should match branches merged)\\n1086:- Source issues closed (count - should match branches merged)\\n1087:- MERGE_READY mails archived (count - should match branches merged)\\n1088:- Test results (pass/fail)\\n1089:- Branches with conflicts (count, names)\\n1090:- Conflict-resolution tasks created (IDs)\\n1091:- Issues filed (if any)\\n1092:- Any escalations sent\\n1093:\\n1094:**Conflict tracking is important** for monitoring MQ health. If many branches\\n1095:conflict, it may indicate target branches are moving too fast or branches are too stale.\\n1096:\\n1097:This becomes the digest when the patrol is squashed.\\n1098:\\n1099:### Step 10: Check integration branches for landing]]>\\n</file>\")] } }]"},"filename":"crates/forge_domain/src/context.rs","line_number":515}
