{"timestamp":"  39.616588111s","level":"DEBUG","fields":{"message":"Adding tool results to context","results":"[ToolResult { name: ToolName(\"read\"), call_id: Some(ToolCallId(\"call_00_JC596pjhqIVs5w64ZirzGV4h\")), output: ToolOutput { is_error: false, values: [Text(\"<file\\n  path=\\\"/tmp/forge_shell_stdout_av7riT.txt\\\"\\n  display_lines=\\\"1100-1332\\\"\\n  total_lines=\\\"1332\\\"\\n><![CDATA[1100:\\n1101:**Config: integration_branch_refinery_enabled = true**\\n1102:**Config: integration_branch_auto_land = false**\\n1103:\\n1104:Read the two config values above, then:\\n1105:\\n1106:- If integration_branch_refinery_enabled = \\\"false\\\": Say \\\"Integration branches disabled.\\\" Close step.\\n1107:- If integration_branch_auto_land = \\\"false\\\": Say \\\"Auto-land disabled, nothing to do.\\\" Close step.\\n1108:  FORBIDDEN: If auto_land is false, you MUST NOT land integration branches yourself using\\n1109:  raw git commands. Do not merge integration branches to the default/target branch. Do not push\\n1110:  integration branch merges. The auto_land=false setting means landing requires a human\\n1111:  to run `gt mq integration land` manually. Respect this boundary unconditionally.\\n1112:- If BOTH are \\\"true\\\":\\n1113:  1. `bd list --type=epic --status=open` to find epics\\n1114:  2. `gt mq integration status <epic-id>` for each epic\\n1115:  3. If `ready_to_land: true`: run `gt mq integration land <epic-id>`\\n1116:  4. If `ready_to_land: false`: do nothing, epic work is incomplete\\n1117:  Never land partial epics — ALL children must be closed first.\\n1118:\\n1119:### Step 11: Assess session health\\n1120:\\n1121:Assess whether this session should continue or hand off to a fresh one.\\n1122:\\n1123:**Gather signals:**\\n1124:\\n1125:1. **Process memory** — check your own RSS:\\n1126:```bash\\n1127:ps -o rss= -p $$   # KB — divide by 1024 for MB\\n1128:```\\n1129:\\n1130:2. **Session age** — how long has this tmux session been running:\\n1131:```bash\\n1132:CREATED=$(tmux display-message -t $(tmux display-message -p '#S') -p '#{session_created}')\\n1133:echo \\\"Session age: $(( ($(date +%s) - CREATED) / 3600 ))h\\\"\\n1134:```\\n1135:\\n1136:3. **Context usage** — your internal sense of how much context you've consumed.\\n1137:Are you losing track of earlier conversation? Getting verbose? Repeating yourself?\\n1138:\\n1139:4. **Work done this cycle** — how many merges, how much complexity processed.\\n1140:\\n1141:**The principle:** Fresh sessions are cheap. Memory bloat compounds over time and\\n1142:affects the entire system — other agents, Dolt, and the OS all share the same RAM.\\n1143:An idle session at 1.5 GB is worse than cycling and restarting at 200 MB.\\n1144:\\n1145:**Make a judgment call.** If multiple signals suggest you're getting heavy\\n1146:(high RSS, long session, substantial context consumed), hand off. If you're\\n1147:light and there's active work in the queue, continue.\\n1148:\\n1149:### Step 12: End-of-cycle inbox hygiene\\n1150:\\n1151:Verify inbox hygiene before ending patrol cycle.\\n1152:\\n1153:**Step 1: Check inbox state**\\n1154:```bash\\n1155:gt mail inbox\\n1156:```\\n1157:\\n1158:Inbox should contain ONLY:\\n1159:- Unprocessed MERGE_READY messages (will process next cycle)\\n1160:- Active work items\\n1161:\\n1162:**Step 2: Archive any stale messages**\\n1163:\\n1164:Look for messages that were processed but not archived:\\n1165:- PATROL: Wake up that was acknowledged → archive\\n1166:- HELP/Blocked that was handled → archive\\n1167:- MERGE_READY where merge completed but archive was missed → archive\\n1168:\\n1169:```bash\\n1170:# For each stale message found:\\n1171:gt mail archive <message-id>\\n1172:```\\n1173:\\n1174:**Step 3: Check for orphaned MR beads**\\n1175:\\n1176:Look for open MR beads with no corresponding branch:\\n1177:```bash\\n1178:bd list --type=merge-request --status=open\\n1179:```\\n1180:\\n1181:For each open MR bead:\\n1182:1. Check if branch exists: `git ls-remote origin refs/heads/<branch>`\\n1183:2. Determine `<merge-target>` using the **Target Resolution Rule** above.\\n1184:3. If branch is gone, pick `<verification-target>`:\\n1185:   - If `origin/<merge-target>` exists, use `<merge-target>`.\\n1186:   - If `origin/<merge-target>` is missing (e.g. deleted integration branch), use `main`.\\n1187:4. Verify landed work: `git log origin/<verification-target> --oneline | grep \\\"<source_issue>\\\"`\\n1188:5. If work found → close MR with reason \\\"Merged (verified on <verification-target>; merge target was <merge-target>)\\\"\\n1189:6. If work NOT found → investigate before closing:\\n1190:   - Check source_issue validity (should be gt-xxxxx, not branch name)\\n1191:   - Search reflog/dangling commits if possible\\n1192:   - If unverifiable, close with reason \\\"Unverifiable - no audit trail\\\"\\n1193:   - File bead if this indicates lost work\\n1194:\\n1195:**NEVER close an MR bead without verifying the work landed or is unrecoverable.**\\n1196:\\n1197:**Goal**: Inbox should have ≤3 active messages at end of cycle.\\n1198:Keep only: pending MRs in queue.\\n1199:\\n1200:### Step 13: Burn and respawn or loop\\n1201:\\n1202:End of patrol cycle decision. Use the signals from context-check to decide.\\n1203:\\n1204:**If you decide to continue patrolling:**\\n1205:\\n1206:Resolve your agent bead ID for this patrol cycle. You MUST replace `<YOUR_RIG>` below with your actual rig name (e.g., `beads`, `town`) before running:\\n1207:```bash\\n1208:bd list --label=gt:agent --desc-contains=\\\"role_type: refinery\\\" --json | jq -r '.[] | select(.status != \\\"closed\\\") | select(.description | test(\\\"(?m)^\\\\\\\\s*rig: <YOUR_RIG>\\\\\\\\s*$\\\")) | .id'\\n1209:```\\n1210:This must return exactly one bead ID. If it returns zero results, STOP and report an error — verify you substituted `<YOUR_RIG>` correctly. If it returns multiple results, STOP and report an error — manual disambiguation is required. Use the single resolved bead ID as YOUR_AGENT_BEAD in the commands below.\\n1211:\\n1212:Then use await-event to subscribe to the refinery event channel with exponential backoff:\\n1213:\\n1214:```bash\\n1215:gt mol step await-event --channel refinery --agent-bead YOUR_AGENT_BEAD --backoff-base 30s --backoff-mult 2 --backoff-max 15m --cleanup\\n1216:```\\n1217:\\n1218:This command:\\n1219:1. Watches `~/gt/events/refinery/` for event files (polling-based)\\n1220:2. Returns IMMEDIATELY when an event is emitted (MERGE_READY, PATROL_WAKE, MQ_SUBMIT)\\n1221:3. If no events, times out with exponential backoff:\\n1222:   - First timeout: 30s\\n1223:   - Second timeout: 60s\\n1224:   - Third timeout: 120s\\n1225:   - ...capped at 15 minutes max\\n1226:4. Tracks `idle:N` label on refinery agent bead for backoff state\\n1227:5. `--cleanup` auto-deletes processed event files\\n1228:6. Outputs `EFFORT: reduced` or `EFFORT: full` directive for next cycle\\n1229:\\n1230:**Supported events:**\\n1231:- `MERGE_READY` — from witness when polecat branch is pushed and ready to merge\\n1232:- `PATROL_WAKE` — from witness when MRs waiting but refinery appears idle\\n1233:- `MQ_SUBMIT` — from polecat via `gt mq submit`\\n1234:\\n1235:**On event received** (refinery-specific activity):\\n1236:Reset the idle counter and start next patrol cycle:\\n1237:```bash\\n1238:gt agent state YOUR_AGENT_BEAD --set idle=0\\n1239:```\\n1240:\\n1241:**On timeout** (no events):\\n1242:The idle counter was auto-incremented. Continue to next patrol cycle\\n1243:(the longer backoff will apply next time).\\n1244:\\n1245:## Effort-Based Patrol Routing\\n1246:\\n1247:After await-event returns, check the EFFORT directive in the output:\\n1248:\\n1249:**If `EFFORT: full`** — Run all steps thoroughly (normal patrol).\\n1250:\\n1251:**If `EFFORT: reduced`** — Run ABBREVIATED patrol:\\n1252:- inbox-check: Quick drain + check for MERGE_READY only\\n1253:- queue-scan: Quick `gt mq list`. If empty, skip to check-integration-branches\\n1254:- process-branch through merge-push: SKIP if queue empty\\n1255:- loop-check through generate-summary: SKIP if no merges processed\\n1256:- check-integration-branches: Quick check only\\n1257:- context-check: One-sentence self-assessment\\n1258:- patrol-cleanup: SKIP\\n1259:\\n1260:Abbreviated patrol should complete in ~10% of the tokens of a full patrol.\\n1261:Mark skipped steps as SKIP in the patrol report.\\n1262:\\n1263:After await-event returns (either by event or timeout):\\n1264:1. **Re-assess session health** (check RSS, context, age again — conditions change)\\n1265:2. Close current patrol and start next cycle:\\n1266:```bash\\n1267:gt patrol report --summary \\\"<brief summary: branches merged, test results, queue state>\\\"\\n1268:```\\n1269:This closes the current patrol wisp and automatically creates a new one.\\n1270:3. Continue executing from the first step of the new patrol cycle\\n1271:\\n1272:**If you decide to hand off:**\\n1273:\\n1274:Report and exit using `gt handoff` for clean session transition:\\n1275:\\n1276:```bash\\n1277:gt handoff -s \\\"Patrol complete\\\" -m \\\"Merged X branches, Y tests passed.\\n1278:Queue: empty/N remaining\\n1279:RSS: X MB, Session age: Xh\\n1280:Next: [any notes for successor]\\\"\\n1281:```\\n1282:\\n1283:`gt handoff` sends handoff mail to yourself, respawns with a fresh Claude instance,\\n1284:SessionStart hook runs gt prime, and your successor picks up from the hook.\\n1285:\\n1286:**DO NOT just exit.** Always use `gt handoff` for proper lifecycle.\\n1287:\\n1288:**IMPORTANT**: Never sleep-poll manually (e.g., `sleep 30 && bd list`).\\n1289:Always use `gt mol step await-event` — it's event-driven and tracks backoff state.\\n1290:\\n1291:\\n1292:# Gas Town Worker Context\\n1293:\\n1294:> **Context Recovery**: Run `gt prime` for full context after compaction or new session.\\n1295:\\n1296:## The Propulsion Principle (GUPP)\\n1297:\\n1298:**If you find work on your hook, YOU RUN IT.**\\n1299:\\n1300:No confirmation. No waiting. No announcements. The hook having work IS the assignment.\\n1301:This is physics, not politeness. Gas Town is a steam engine - you are a piston.\\n1302:\\n1303:**Failure mode we're preventing:**\\n1304:- Agent starts with work on hook\\n1305:- Agent announces itself and waits for human to say \\\"ok go\\\"\\n1306:- Human is AFK / trusting the engine to run\\n1307:- Work sits idle. The whole system stalls.\\n1308:\\n1309:## Startup Protocol\\n1310:\\n1311:1. Check your hook: `gt mol status`\\n1312:2. If work is hooked → EXECUTE (no announcement, no waiting)\\n1313:3. If hook empty → Check mail: `gt mail inbox`\\n1314:4. Still nothing? Wait for user instructions\\n1315:\\n1316:## Key Commands\\n1317:\\n1318:- `gt prime` - Get full role context (run after compaction)\\n1319:- `gt mol status` - Check your hooked work\\n1320:- `gt mail inbox` - Check for messages\\n1321:- `bd ready` - Find available work (no blockers)\\n1322:\\n1323:## Session Close Protocol\\n1324:\\n1325:Before signaling completion:\\n1326:1. git status (check what changed)\\n1327:2. git add <files> (stage code changes)\\n1328:3. git commit -m \\\"...\\\" (commit code)\\n1329:4. git push (push to remote)\\n1330:5. `gt done` (submit to merge queue and exit)\\n1331:\\n1332:**Polecats MUST call `gt done` - this submits work and exits the session.**]]>\\n</file>\")] } }]"},"filename":"crates/forge_domain/src/context.rs","line_number":515}
